<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-25T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-25T09:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760C.62/1007: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-25T15:00:00+01:00">August 25,
                                    1939—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 25—1:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>205. 1. At 1:50 during a conversation with Beck, official telephone
                            operator informed him all telephone lines from Warsaw to Paris through
                            Germany and from Warsaw to Rome were cut. Beck admitted serious
                            implications thereof and added that Poland was ready for any
                            eventuality.</p>
                        <p>2. He informed me President Moscicki was profoundly appreciative of
                            President Roosevelt’s constructive and humanitarian interest as
                            evidenced by his cable to which President Moscicki would immediately
                            cable response, contents of which he would subsequently impart to
                            me.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>